I have been delving in the code and I have found a solution which appears to work. Unfortunately, it does involve modifying code. The particular piece of code which needs modifying is the 
```text
generate_
sql
()
```
 method in the `data_field_text` and `data_field_textarea` classes. The following code is based on Moodle 1.9.3+ (Build: 20081119) ‚ÄîI know we should upgrade, but it has been low priority because it is an internal server . 
```text
 function generate_sql($tablealias, $value) {


 /*


 * Original code


 */


 // return " ({$tablealias}.fieldid = {$this->field->id} AND {$tablealias}.content LIKE '%{$value}%') "; 


 /*


 * Modified code


 */


 $sql = " ({$tablealias}.fieldid = {$this->field->id}"; 


 foreach (explode(" ", $value) as $val) {


 $sql .= " AND {$tablealias}.content LIKE '%{$val}%'";


 }


 $sql .= ") ";
```
 Glancing at the latest code from CVS , it appears that those methods have been modified since our server was installed, so my modifications will need changing. So that seems to work, but it doesn't feel very satisfying. If anyone has a better suggestion‚Äîparticularly one which does not involve modifying code‚ÄîI would love to hear it.
